The occupant of this position will be part of the Software Development Group
in the Development & System Transition (D&ST) directorate, which is comprised
of 82 employees and a rotation of contractors. This position reports to the
Manager of Development.

We value diversity and are actively seeking candidates with varied backgrounds
who can think differently and innovate. In choosing the right person for this
role we will consider what you have done previously - the knowledge, skills
and experience you've built, your potential for development, and your personal
qualities.

The Queensland Police Service provides a supportive, people-focussed work
environment that supports work life balance and flexible work options.

** Your key accountabilities: **

_ ** The core capability requirements for this role are: ** _

  * Develop and implement strategic direction for business application software development whilst liaising with the design and architecture teams to ensure a high level of service is provided. 
  * Ensure design, coding, documentation and testing of the code written by the team is completed in accordance with best-practice software development, IDS guidelines and PDM methodologies. 
  * Participate in Agile software development practices, including sprint planning, daily stand-ups, and sprint retrospectives. 
  * Maintain documentation for Software Development Group solutions, including design documents, technical specifications, and user guides. 
  * Solve complex technical problems and provide technical direction to other developers. 
  * Provide expert advice on business system solutions, products, implementation, transition and services and provide support and guidance to internal and external stakeholders. 
  * Provide leadership and work collaboratively with team members to develop their technical skills and knowledge. 

** Role Requirements: **

_ ** Qualification: ** _

  * A tertiary level qualification in Information Technology or Computer is highly desirable 

_ ** Technical/Operational/Educational experience: ** _

** Demonstrated use and skill with the following technologies: **

  * Microsoft.NET Framework/Core (C#) 
  * Java 
  * Microsoft Design Patterns (MVC, MVVM, Razor) 
  * Microsoft Visual Studio 2022 
  * Azure DevOps, TeamCity, DevOps 
  * Testing Frameworks (MSTest, NUnit, Gherkin, SpecFlow) 
  * Entity Framework / Dapper / SQL 
  * Microsoft Web Services technologies 

Strong knowledge in all phases of the System Development Lifecycle (SDLC)
Commitment to maintain currency with industry trends and technological  
advancements

_ ** Desirable Skills/Requirements: ** _

  * Knowledge of developing within a Secure Software Development Lifecycle 
  * Demonstrated experience in Cross Functional Agile teams 
  * Knowledge of Java development technologies 
  * Knowledge of Microsoft Web Platform 

